h8201.definition: from {{h8199}}; a sentence, i.e. infliction; judgment.

h8202.definition: from {{h8199}}; judge; Shaphat, the name of four Israelites; Shaphat.

h8205.definition: from {{h8192}}; bareness; concretely, a bare hill or plain; high place, stick out.

h8209.definition: (Aramaic) intensive of a form corresponding to {{h8208}}; beautiful; fair.

h8212.definition: feminine of a derivative from {{h8210}}; a pipe (for pouring forth, e.g. wine), i.e. the penis; privy member.

h8217.definition: from {{h8213}}; depressed, literally or figuratively; base(-st), humble, low(-er, -ly).

h8219.definition: from {{h8213}}; Lowland, i.e. (with the article) the maritime slope of Palestine; low country, (low) plain, vale(-ley).

h8254.definition: a primitive root; to suspend or poise (especially in trade); pay, receive(-r), spend, × throughly, weigh.

h8255.definition: from {{h8254}}; probably a weight; used as a commercial standard; shekel.

h8256.definition: or (feminine) שִׁקְמָה; of uncertain derivation; a sycamore (usually the tree); sycamore (fruit, tree).

h8265.definition: a primitive root; to ogle, i.e. blink coquettishly; wanton.

h8270.definition: from {{h8324}}; (compare {{h8306}}); a string (as twisted ), i.e. (specifically) the umbilical cord (also figuratively, as the centre of strength); navel.

h8272.definition: of foreign derivation; Sharetser, the name of an Assyrian and an Israelite; Sharezer.

h8275.definition: for {{h7626}}; a rod of empire; sceptre.

h8276.definition: a primitive root; to intwine; wrap together, wreath.

h8277.definition: a primitive root; (compare {{h8279}}); properly, to puncture, i.e. (figuratively through the idea of slipping out) to escape or survive; remain.

h8278.definition: from {{h8277}}; stitching (as pierced with a needle); service.

h8279.definition: from {{h8277}}; a (carpenter's) scribing-awl (for pricking or scratching measurements); line.

h8280.definition: a primitive root; to prevail; have power (as a prince).

h8282.definition: feminine of {{h8269}}; a mistress, i.e. female noble; lady, princess, queen.

h8283.definition: the same as {{h8282}}; Sarah, Abraham's wife; Sarah.

h8286.definition: from {{h8276}}; tendril; Serug, a postdiluvian patriarch; Serug.

h8288.definition: from {{h8308}}; a thong (as laced or tied); (shoe-)latchet.

h8290.definition: patrial from {{h8289}}; a Sharonite or inhabitant of Sharon; Sharonite.

h8291.definition: passive participle from the same as {{h8321}}; a grapevine; principal plant. See {{h8320}}, {{h8321}}.

h8292.definition: or (by permutation) שְׁרִיקָה; feminine passive participle of {{h8319}}; a whistling (in scorn); by analogy, a piping; bleating, hissing.

h8294.definition: by permutation for {{h5629}}; superfluity; Serach, an Israelitess; Sarah, Serah.

h8296.definition: and שָׂרֶטֶת; from {{h8295}}; an incision; cutting.

h8297.definition: from {{h8269}}; dominative; Sarai, the wife of Abraham; Sarai.

h8298.definition: probably from {{h8324}}; hostile; Sharay, an Israelite; Sharai.

h8300.definition: from {{h8277}}; a survivor; × alive, left, remain(-ing), remnant, rest.
